tton></div></div><div class=3D"comment-body"><p><span>I think Berlin was ju=
st plain wrong about this.  Justice and Freedom, rather than being irreconc=
ilable opposites, are better conceptualized as being the way Ernest Hemingw=
ay described men's relationship with women: you can't live with them and yo=
u can't live without them.  In other words, there is a kind of interdepende=
nce between opposites.</span></p><p><span>Thus, for instance, a society tha=
t values liberty with no thought of justice is liable to end up with neithe=
r, with one strong man at the top.  Likewise, a society that claims to valu=
e justice with no thought of liberty (like the old Soviet Union) ended up w=
ith a nomenklatura.</span></p><p><span>The challenge is to reconcile the tw=
o within limits.    To give a concrete example in the field of public finan=
ce, consider this possibility of reconciling great inequality with justice =
and liberty: </span></p><p><span><a href=3D"https://docs.google.com/documen=
t/d/1WIdVnQEWdYgYYly9iKkesWCVhfINvbtwuVq2GMOxMbw/edit?usp=3Dsharing" class=
=3D"linkified" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow ugc noopener">https://docs=
.google.com/document/d/1WIdVnQEWdYgYYly9iKkesWCVhfINvbtwuVq2GMOxMbw/edit?us=
p=3Dsharing</a></span></p><p><span>I'm a hedgehog by the way.  Wasn't a cho=
ice, I was born that way.</span></p><div role=3D"button" class=3D"show-all-=
